 {"id":"asupersync-14o","title":"[EPIC-TOKIO] Tokio Ecosystem Feature Parity - Complete Runtime Capabilities","description":"# Tokio Ecosystem Feature Parity

## Goal
Achieve full feature parity with the tokio async runtime ecosystem while implementing everything from first principles with Asupersync's core invariants:
- Structured concurrency (no orphan tasks)
- Cancel-correctness (protocol, not flag)  
- Two-phase effects (no data loss)
- Capability security (all through Cx)
- Deterministic testing (lab runtime)

## Scope
This epic covers implementing native equivalents for ALL major tokio ecosystem components:

### Core Runtime (Phase 1)
- Multi-threaded scheduler with work stealing
- spawn(), spawn_blocking(), spawn_local() equivalents
- Runtime configuration and tuning
- Region-based parallelism

### Networking (Phase 2+)
- TCP (TcpListener, TcpStream)
- UDP (UdpSocket)  
- Unix sockets (UnixListener, UnixStream, UnixDatagram)
- All with cancel-correct I/O obligations

### Filesystem (Phase 2+)
- Async file operations (read, write, create, delete)
- Directory operations
- All with proper cancel-safety

### Synchronization Primitives
- Mutex, RwLock (cancel-aware)
- Semaphore with two-phase permits
- Barrier
- Notify
- OnceCell

### Time
- Virtual time (lab) and wall time (production)
- sleep(), sleep_until()
- interval(), interval_at()
- Deadline integration with budgets

### Streams
- Stream trait
- Comprehensive StreamExt combinators
- Channel-to-stream wrappers

### I/O Traits
- AsyncRead, AsyncWrite (with obligations)
- AsyncBufRead, AsyncSeek
- Buffered I/O
- Copy operations

### Codecs (tokio-util)
- Decoder/Encoder traits
- Framed transport
- Common codecs (lines, length-delimited, etc.)

### Service Layer (tower)
- Service trait
- Layer composition
- Standard middleware stack

### HTTP (hyper equivalent)
- HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2
- Client and Server
- Native cancel-correct implementation

### gRPC (tonic equivalent)
- All streaming patterns
- Protobuf integration
- Service definitions

## Success Criteria
- All features implemented from first principles
- All honor Asupersync invariants
- Comprehensive test coverage
- Deterministic testing possible for all components
- Documentation with examples

## Non-Goals
- Exact API compatibility with tokio (our APIs reflect our semantics)
- Wrapping tokio (we implement everything ourselves)
